BLOCK E – Decomposition & Visualization of Threat Intelligence

Time: 30–40 minutes

Goal: Learn how security analysts break down attacks into smaller pieces and visualize them for investigation and decision-making.


---

1. What is Decomposition?

Decomposition means:

> Breaking a complex cyber attack into smaller, understandable parts.



Instead of saying:

> "The bank was hacked."



We ask:

How did the attacker enter?

What vulnerability was exploited?

What tools were used?

Which systems were affected?

What data was targeted?



---

Example

Attack:

Customer receives phishing email
        ↓
Clicks malicious link
        ↓
Credentials stolen
        ↓
Attacker logs into VPN
        ↓
Accesses internal application
        ↓
Steals customer data

Instead of one event, we now have six attack stages.


---

2. Why Decompose an Attack?

Benefits:

Easier investigation

Easier detection

Easier reporting

Easier mitigation

Helps identify the root cause


Instead of fixing only the final breach, you can stop the attack earlier.


---

